quran[21]{c,v,t}:
  44,19,"Do not set yourselves above God: I bring you clear authority"
  44,20,"I have sought refuge with my Lord and your Lord lest you stone me [to death]"
  44,21,"If you do not believe in me, at least keep away from me"
  44,22,"Then he cried out to his Lord, \"These are sinful people"
  44,23,"God said, \"Set out with My servants by night, for you will certainly be pursued"
  44,24,Leave the sea behind you parted; they are a host destined to be drowned
  44,25,How many gardens and fountains they left behind them
  44,26,and cornfields and splendid buildings
  44,27,and pleasant things in which they delighted
  44,28,"Such was their end, and what had been theirs We gave to other people to inherit"
  44,29,"Neither heaven nor earth wept for them, nor were they allowed any respite"
  44,30,We saved the Children of Israel from their humiliating torment
  44,31,"at the hands of Pharaoh: he was a tyrant who exceeded all bounds"
  44,32,We knowingly chose them above all other people
  44,33,and showed them signs in which there was a clear test
  44,34,Yet those who deny the truth say
  44,35,there is nothing beyond our first death; we shall not be raised again
  44,36,"So bring our fathers [back], if what you say is true"
  44,37,"Are they better than the people of Tubba' and those who came before them? We destroyed them, because they were guilty of sin"
  44,38,We did not idly create the heavens and the earth and all that lies between them
  44,39,"We did not create them save with a purpose, yet most people have no knowledge of this"